    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: HORTON ON/OFF - FAN BLADES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>FAN BLADES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>There are two types of fan blade assemblies used with the Horton On/Off Fan Clutch Assembly.
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200424">Figure 24</hotlnk>shows a fan assembly with plastic fan blades.
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200425">Figure 25</hotlnk>shows an all steel fan blade assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200424" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200424" filename="../figg12/G1200424.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Plastic Fan Blade Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. METAL HUB</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PLASTIC FAN BLADES (9)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNTING HOLES (6)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1200425" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200425" filename="../figg12/G1200425.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Steel Fan Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FAN BLADE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPIDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RIVETS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
